The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems, specifically minimum cycle basis, all-pairs min cut, and Gomory-Hu tree, which are all topics in the area of graph theory and algorithms. The use of planar graphs and the focus on subquadratic time and space complexity suggest that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of optimization techniques and the emphasis on weights and distances also suggest that the paper may belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
